MSG 01
Notice that there is a new instruction available: ADD
MSG_END

MSG 02
Usage:
ADD OP1, OP2
does OP1 + OP2 and stores the result in OP1
MSG_END

MSG 03
Solve the challenge using the MOV and ADD instructions
MSG_END

+++LEVEL ENDS 05

+++LEVEL STARTS 06

QUANTITY 3

MSG 00
Level 07
MSG_END

MSG 01
Did you know that MOV and ADD can be used with both operands being registers?
MSG_END

MSG 02
Example:
MOV rbx, rax
moves the value from rax to rbx
MSG_END

+++LEVEL ENDS 06

+++LEVEL STARTS 07

QUANTITY 3

MSG 00
Level 08
MSG_END

MSG 01
Both operands of instructions MOV and ADD can be the same register
MSG_END

MSG 02
Example:
ADD rax, rax
does rax + rax and stores the result in rax
MSG_END

